<section class="block-section story">
  <span class="section-tag">Story</span>
  <h2>Why this block matters</h2>
  <p class="sub">First real work day on the Landscape Reading. Location locked. Biography started.</p>
  <p>The first 15 minutes is teacher conferencing — your location locks today. From this block forward, every <a href="/units/unit-2/assessment-landscape-reading/">Landscape Reading</a> activity is on YOUR place. The middle 50 minutes is independent work: Google Earth (with historical imagery), GSI / Bhuvan maps, the curated photos for your location. The closing 15 is a paired peer-check protocol — designed to catch missing evidence and questionable inferences early, before they're baked into your draft.</p>
  <p>The peer-check is not feedback yet. It's an evidence audit. The question your partner asks is one of two: <em>"what's the evidence for that?"</em> or <em>"what's missing?"</em>. That's it. The actual rubric-based peer feedback happens in Block 8 after the worked example in Block 7.</p>
</section>

