<section class="block-section do">
  <span class="section-tag">Do</span>
  <h2>Today's work — choose one path</h2>
  <p class="sub">First 15 min: teacher conferencing to lock locations. Then 50 minutes of work, then 15 minutes of peer-check. The path you pick is about how to spend the middle 50.</p>
  <div class="choice-intro">
    <strong>Learning Intention:</strong> I have my Landscape Reading location locked AND a first draft of the past + present biography sections with at least 3 cited sources.
  </div>
  <div class="choice-board">
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">A</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Past + present sections (default)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Work the biography template through Steps 3 + 4 — the deep-past + recent-past biography and the current-processes section. Get to "rough draft" status on both. Cite at least 3 sources by the end of the block.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Default</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">B</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Past + present + projections (stretch)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Same as A, plus rough-draft the projections section (Step 5). For students who already have strong evidence and want to get ahead before the worked-example day. Use Field Geologist for hard projections.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Stretch</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">C</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Strengthen your weakest section (choice)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">If your Block 5 reflection flagged a specific weak spot (a process you don't fully understand, a source you don't trust, a timescale you're shaky on), spend the block on that. Targeted &gt; broad on this kind of work day.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Choice</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">D</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Google Earth historical-imagery peer-help (practice)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">If you can't get the historical-imagery slider to work, or aren't sure what to look for in older imagery, come to the peer-help station. A student who's comfortable with Google Earth walks you through it on your location.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Pairs · Practice</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="block-section show">
  <span class="section-tag">Show</span>
  <h2>What you're submitting today</h2>
  <p class="sub">Location locked + Components 1 &amp; 2 (K/U) of the Landscape Reading lock today.</p>
  <div class="submission-callout">
    <div class="label">Location locked + biography-past (Component 1) + current-processes (Component 2)</div>
    <p>Three things in your dossier folder: (1) location confirmation written down (a one-liner naming your location is enough — "I'm doing Marina Beach, the segment north of the lighthouse"). (2) <strong>Component 1 — landscape biography (past)</strong>: Step 3 from the <a href="/units/unit-2/assessment-landscape-reading/">Landscape Reading</a>, ≥4 timepoints with the right processes and vocabulary for each era. (3) <strong>Component 2 — current processes</strong>: Step 4, 3–4 active processes each with evidence. Both are <strong>K/U components and they lock today</strong> — you get a strand band on each that becomes part of your overall K/U mark.</p>
    <a href="#" class="rubric-link">Submit via Google Classroom →</a>
  </div>
  <p class="rubric-meta">
    <strong>Rubric link:</strong> Components 1 and 2 are K/U — correct processes, accurate mechanisms, time periods, and discipline-specific vocabulary. These are the first two locks in the <a href="/units/unit-2/assessment-landscape-reading/">rolling-summative</a> sequence; the bands you get today don't re-mark at the end. See the <a href="/foundations/the-rubric/">rubric</a>.
  </p>
</section>

